A good proof that cigarettes are an intuitive object is that even non-smokers never accidentally burn themselves while smoking a cigarette. Even if you have never held one before you intuitively know how to hold and maneuver it around as not to accidentally burn yourself with it.

Knives are the opposite, even experienced chefs often cut their fingers while chopping stuff, if you give a child a bushcraft knife he will 100% cut himself while whittling wood or cutting something, but you will never hear a story of anyone burning his eye out with a cigarette.
Do not start smoking cigarettes. Maybe try a cigar if you are interested.

It's common in paranormal stories for someone to "bribe" a ghost with a pack of cigarettes as an offering or to find a cigarette placed somewhe as a "gift" from the entity. The intuitive nature of the cigarette as an object make it a perfect impromptu currency for trade, barter.

I've heard in China it's common for people to bring a pack of cigarettes as a bribe for a doctor during a hospital visit, cigarettes become the default currency for soldiers and people in prison, etc. It's no wonder ghosts understand this and are ready to use them that way too...
